text: Kentucky is bourbon country, and this beer surely wont change any hearts and minds on that subject, but theres always a chance. Somehow, Kentucky Ryed Chiquen manages to capture lots of whiskey character while still drinking like a beer. Caramel brown color. Spicy rye and oak on the nose. Flavor has boozy sweetness - like charred sugar and butterscotch - and a very mellow oaky note. For all the whiskey taste, this goes down with smoothness and just a touch of pleasant heat. In typical AtG fashion, this brew comes off as a joke but drinks like something made with a lot of care and thought.

(Thanks, Brandon Clownoisseur)

Bottle.

A- Whisky, butterscotch, sugar cookies.

A- Brown red color, cloudy liquid, off white head.

T- Whisky, butterscotch, molasses, caramel, oak, medium sweetness, vanilla.

P- Medium body, average texture, average carbonation, balanced finish.

O-First off, what a cool bottle. A tad disappointed it doesnt actually taste like chicken. Just kidding that would be awful. This bottle was a gusher. Other than that it was good stuff. Lots of butterscotch and masks the booze well. Drinks easy and tastes great.

Sampled from bottle shared by Joes. Unclear dark orange to reddish color, average sized off-white to beige head. Dont get much aroma. Taste malts, slightly hops, caramel, brown candy sugar. Decent body and carbonation.
Bottle @ joes. Amber colour with a medium sized off-white head. Smells sweet, malty, chocolate. Tastes nutty, sweet, malts, caramel. Medium to full body, soft carbo.

Massive rye whisky bomb, dry and boozy as hell, the liquor pretty much the dominant characteristic. Some caramel comes through, maybe a bit of toffee and chocolate, but mostly we get rye whisky and nothing but rye whisky. Mild oak on the finish, maybe a hint of floral hop bitterness. Probably not. Might as well get a shot.
Amber pour. Aroma is vanilla and caramel with rye whiskey. Flavor is sweet vanilla with oaky and fruity esters. Full bodied and full flavored. aokbyme
Slodki aromat zdominowany przez beczke. Whisky mo?e brandy. I kwiaty. S: kwaskowe, wodniste, delikatny szlachetny alkohol i w finiszu zbozowe, mo?e chlebowe.

Ciekawy, swojski aromat pieczonego chleba, dębu, wiśni. W smaku gładkie, aksamitne, ułożone. Smak chleba razowego, ciemnych słodów, melasy, ciut pumperniklu, toffi i beczka. Słodkie i przyjemne dla podniebienia. Lekki akcent owocowy w tle - wiśnie.
Bottle. Pours dark amber with a small off-white head. Aroma of rye, bourbon, light fruit, oak and caramel. Flavor of caramel, vanilla, bourbon, oak, rye and some dried fruit.
How: tap Appearance; hazy dark amber, medium white head. Aroma: stone fruits,, wood, hay, some mild citrus notes. Palate: medium body, average carbonation.
Tap at Hoppy Gnome. Red orange with a white head. Toffee, dried cherry, woody and faint whiskey aromas. Woody and earthy flavors, mostly dry. Medium body with a smooth feel.

Tasted from the tap on the 04/02/2017. Orange to amber colour with a big off-white head. Aroma of sweet fruits, caramel and spices. More wood on the taste than in the aroma. Taste has some spices, hints of caramel and sweet fruits. Next one please!

Aroma and taste is sweet toasted malty, rye, some sweet caramel action, fruity notes, dried fruit, bourbon soaked wooden accents into the close.

On tap. Pours a dark mahogany color with a small head. Aroma of fairly muted with rye, bit of caramel and dark fruit. Taste of caramel, dark fruit and rye. No real bitterness and fairly clean finish. Moderate body, smooth with a slight malty feel. No hint of the 8.6% ABV. enjoyable beer to relax with.

Underwhelming aroma, unique brown color, nice rye barrel flavor, slightly boozy with a smooth palate. Overall good and different. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Tap at Js. Pours a clear, deep gold to light amber with a half-finger of foam that dissipates quickly. Malty nose with some light caramel and rye bread notes. Clean and crisp amber. Faint barrel notes on the finish: vanilla and whisky and more malt.
Very sweet aroma, slight maize and bourbon. Flavor is much like the aroma. Sweet, light bourbon, light rye. Thin across the palate.

750 ml bottle, Cardinal Pub & Bar, Stavanger. ABV is 8.6%. Orange to amber colour, huge off-white head. Distinct aroma of rye whiskey oak barrel, hints of caramel and dark dried fruits. The flavour has a slight malty sweetness, again followed by notes of rye whiskey or bourbon oak barrel, caramel and brown sugar, dark dried fruits and mild spices. Moderate hops. Overcarbonated, fizzy mouthfeel.

Fra flaske (kveldens siste) på Mi2 Cardinal nov-16: lett uklar lys gylden med ok skum. Interessant duft og smak av karamell, krydder, grillet kjøtt, og appelsiner sammen med rugsyre og noe bær. En fin avslutning på nok en hyggelig kveld!
Backlog, ocena przepisana z untappd, w ramach uzupełniania profilu na ratebeer.

Sporo aromatu beczki pod postacią mokrego drewna z dodatkiem czerwonych owoców, lekkiego karmelu i pikanterii żyta. W smaku pełne, lekko oleiste, wytrawnie karmelowe z lekką kwaskowatością i świetnym już stricte bourbonowym finiszem. Świetne !

Draught at Fermentoren. Medium high white fluffy lasting head. Hazy dark amber body. Fruity acidic aroma. Smooth and pleasant fruity acidic flavor with a little bit of vanilla. Low on bitterness, low carbonation, long finish.

Pours dark amber with a small offwhite head. Aroma of malt, rye, light sourness, bread, light fruit, oak, bourbon. Flavor is malt, rich caramel, cocoa, chocolate, vanilla, oak, bourbon. Medium body, soft carbonation, dry finish.

Smells a little nutty, a little barrelesc, a bit of heat from the whiskey. Glowing brown with light cover of head. Smooth almost mellow milk chocolate then then a woody vanilla carries it home. Amazing great smooth body.

[email protected]/* <![CDATA[ */!function(t,e,r,n,c,a,p){try{t=document.currentScript||function(){for(t=document.getElementsByTagName('script'),e=t.length;e--;)if(t[e].getAttribute('data-cfhash'))return t[e]}();if(t&&(c=t.previousSibling)){p=t.parentNode;if(a=c.getAttribute('data-cfemail')){for(e='',r='0x'+a.substr(0,2)|0,n=2;a.length-n;n+=2)e+='%'+('0'+('0x'+a.substr(n,2)^r).toString(16)).slice(-2);p.replaceChild(document.createTextNode(decodeURIComponent(e)),c)}p.removeChild(t)}}catch(u){}}()/* ]]> */ Amber haze. One finger foam. Bourbon malty notes. Alcoholic caramalte tone. Oak backbone. Nice complex in any Way. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Draft. Pours a medium, well retained, ivory head, with heavy lacing, over a slightly hazy copper (SRM 15) body......nose is rye, light bourbon, hints of oak, light bread, biscuit, balanced.......taste is slightly sweet with caramel hints, light bourbon notes, heavy rye, hints of oak and vanilla, mild hop bitterness on the finish.....mouth feel, medium body, moderate alcohol heat, moderate carbonation. This is a well made showcase for the rye, with nicely handled barrel notes, mild hops. BJCP 8/3/13/4/7

Aroma: vanilla, bourbon, caramel
Taste: light bitter, lubie light sweet, vanilla, oak, marshmallows, fruity, caramel

A nice bourbon rye overall. Pours a cloudy Amber with a tan head. Smells of cherries, strawberries and a bit of caramel and vanilla. Taste is crisp, like a pale ale, with some bourbon and vanilla. Had in the bottle.
Pours a dark mahogany brown with fluffy head. Aromas of bourbon, malts, citrus hops. Flavors of light malt, booze and some sweetness

Bottle thanks to Rob. Pours a dark hazy copper with medium off white head leaving spotty lacing. The aroma is rye, wood and bourbon. Medium mouth, rye, bourbon, oak, spice, nice dry finish, very good.

75cl bottle shared with friends. Somewhat hazy amber / golden with a small white head. Full body with low to moderate carbonation. Well balanced sweet and bitter tones. Caramel, malts, bourbon, rye and some fruits. Very nice.

Bottle from starcross -- cheers! Opened at a tasting of barrel-aged beers, and this one came across as distinctly "light". Theres some good rye flavor (somewhere between spiciness and earthiness), and the aroma of rye whisky is definitely there. However, its a bit too muddled and sticky, and it didnt stand out next to a lot of the other beers we tried.
On tap at Taps. Pours a pale brown color with a bit of head. Mild maltiness and minimal barrel flavor.

An aroma of rye whiskey and dried fruit with a hint of malt. Pours a clear bourbon color with an off white head with decent laci g. Tastes like a fruity rye whiskey with a sweet malt whiskey finish. Medium body.

.66l bottle from Firmabier. Pours cloudy apricot color with high foamy, off white head. Aroma is dried fruits, exotic fruit notes, grape fruit notes, hops, malts, alcohol, syrup, caramel, bread. Flavor is mostly same. Well balanced, bubbly mouth feel. Swell!

Poured into a snifter.

3.75 A: Mildly hazed rose/light amber color. Two fingers of creamy beige head. Retention is pretty good and a short ring of lacing is left.

3.75 S: Hmm, this is interesting. To start, the rye malt isnt nearly as strong as I was expecting. A lot of rye beers Ive had would mop the floor with this one. That said, theres TONS of rye whiskey aroma. Its tangy, earthy, and boozy. Less of the spicy earthiness that comes with rye malt. Still its a very nice nose. Light caramel and toasty notes.

3.5 T: The taste is like the nose, but calmer. Less boozy than the nose suggests - indeed its pretty much undetectable. Tangy, earthy, leather rye whiskey. Spicy earthiness, caramel, toastiness, light non-sweet toffee.

3.5 M: Medium to heavier medium body. Good moderate carbonation. Super smooth with a light warming finish, but lacking creaminess.

3.5 D: Pretty good beer. Not great, but well balanced with easy drinkability.

★ 973 characters


DavoleBomb, Oct 14, 2015

On tap at Global Brew.  Pours an orange/gold with a thin off white head. Decidedly fruity aroma. Taste is sweet caramel malt, buttery, fruitiness once again, and a whiskey character that is not overdone. Tart, but not sour. Good stuff.

Bottled. Amber coloured. Unclear. Dense light amber coloured. Aroma. Caramel, sweetness, some herbs, spice. Flavour. Caramel, fruits, sweetnesd, herbs, spice. Medium bodied. Ends sweft and fruity with light bitterness.

Butelka. Barwa pomarańczowo-czerwona, klarowna. Piana wysoka, kremowa, powoli opadająca. \piana utrzymuje się do samego końca dodatkowo ładnie zdobi szkło. Aromat delikatnej beczki, owoce, karmel. W smaku brak posmaków pikantnych, o której mowa w opisie. Bardzo owocowe, miodowe, słodowe. Posmaki beczki, drewna wyraźne w miarę ogrzewania się piwa. Jak dla mnie zdecydowanie zbyt mało wyraziste. Wysycenie w kierunku wysokiego, goryczka niska niezalegająca. Świetna pijalność. Oczekiwania były większe, lekkie rozczarowanie. Cena nie współmierna do jakości.

Bottle 66cl / Botella 66cl. 
@ Zombier, Malaga, España.
A: Amber / Ambar. 
T/S: Malt, sweet, rye, alcohol / Malta, dulce, centeno, alcohol.
Draft at Mikkeller - sweet aroma. Nice Amber reddish color. Amber really allows the bourbon flavored to shine through. Deceiving ply deniable for a 9% beer. Clean palate.
UPDATED: APR 23, 2017 Backlog. Tap @ Mikkeller & Friends, Copenhagen 20131016. Fruity and caramely with a dry finish.

Light orange zest and rye whiskey aromas, some oak and more whiskey as it warms. Taste is whiskey, peach, orange zest, rye crackers, caramel and marmalade. Coconut barrel character really shines in the finish when it has warmed.
Bottle. It poured a clear amber color with an off-white head. The aroma was of dark sugars, bourbon and some fruits. The taste was similar to the aroma with more bourbon, fruits and malts. Decent.
Tap at Clubhouse BFD. Pours deep maker, white head. Aroma is sweet berry, bourbon, caramel, vanilla. Interesting. Flavor is malt, caramel, light bourbon barrel character. Its ok.
Reddish brown pour, big frothy light brown head. Spicy rye aroma, hints of baked bread. Flavor is mostly rye, hints of wood and toffee. Interesting, but a one time bye.

Tap @ basement beer bar. Aroma of fruity caramel, bourbon, spicy. Clear dark amber with white head, not lasting. Moderate sweetness, light+ bitterness, spicy. Medium body, watery+ texture, avg. carb., sweet bourbon finish.

Sample at the Daily Growler 3rd Anniversary on 12/17/15. Pours clear amber with a medium beige head. Nose of sweet malt, light caramel, spicy rye malt and whiskey. Malty and caramelly flavor with spicy rye accents before a mildly boozy finish.

Bottle thanks to Matt! Bit of a slow gusher on opening. Pours murky hazel, medium beige head, nice residual and lacing. Aroma is spicy rye, hints of whiskey. Flavor is light plus sweet, light bitter, rye malts and rye whiskey leave a pretty prominent mark on the flavor profile. Medium body, high carbonation.

750 ml bottle poured a clear orange amber with a small lasting amber head. Aromas of rye, oak, vanilla, rye ehiskey and fruitiness. Palate was light to medium bodied and smooth with a dry finish. Flavors of rye, oak, fruitiness, light vanilla and light whiskey with a smooth dry lingeting rye finish.

Aroma: caramel, toffee malts, grain (maybe rye), wood, touch of whiskey. Appearance: slightly hazy, light dark brown, small, creamy, white head. Taste: medium sweet. Palate: sweets continue, fairly heavy, caramel, toffee malts, straw, dust, light fruitiness. Overall: OK BA beer, a touch on the sweet side. Port Street Brew House, Manchester.

Keg at PSBH, Manchester. Slight hazy amber shade. Thin head. Notes of toffee, golden syrup, nuts and whiskey. Taste adds to those elements with a fruitier orangey slant. Quite good but not nearly as punchy as I expected. Its been on for a while here and maybe suffering for it.
KRS 140815. Red amber colour with an off-white head. Aroma and flavour is dried fruit, grass, pine, rye, malt, berries, fruit, hop, bread, alcohol, spices. Full body. Nice beer.

bottle from ølbutikken i think, or kihoskh. clear brown, smooth light brown head.
finest burbon, malts and wood aroma, resembling a good barley wine that is not hopped a lot.
flavor is malts, boozy notes, bitter caramel, licorice. A bit too thin and bitter caramel like compared to what i would expect from aroma, more speciality grain than barley wine. The bitter hops are now more prominent, but still very european. tasty brew, almost an 8 bit just misses that bc it lacks a little malt flavor as i sense it. This is pretty impressively done if it is the first barrel aged out of the brewery.

Bottle, 0.75l, shared with Luka. Pours hazy brownish amber color with medium soapy tan-like head and average sparkling appearance. Aroma of grains, dark fruits, wood, whiskey and some honey. Taste starts with moderate sweet caramel and honey, follows by mild fruity acidity, whiskey and barrel note, mouthfeel is warming and alcoholic, while finish is moderate bitter. Medium to full body, syrupy texture and lively average carbonation in palate. Not the best, but I liked it more than Catcher in the Rye...

Sampled draft @ Delirium Hoppy Loft. Deep red amber, little head. Nose is hugely sweet weird caramel, boozy alcoholic apple, spirit, cough syrup, weird very sweet alcoholic spirit cough syrup. Taste is touch watery, weirdly sweet alcoholic apple, lightly vegetable, spirit, very sweet cough syrup, cooked apple, very strong tea that stood for far too long, apple, thick raisins, oak, Bit watery, crazily sweet,. Very odd, not even sure what this one was meant to be. At least the barrel didnt have chicken feathers stuck to it (I think). Touch bizarre appealing but overall not really for me.

Man. Fudge this beer! .. Feather on the bottle, thats about as good as it gets .. . Dirty rye underwear .. Sad plucky mouth, medium to long stained finish .. Not good and horribly shitily over priced .. . . My cats butt looks like a car lighter

Ładny złożony aromat: karmel, susz owocowy, niuanse waniliowe. W smaku wyraźna gładkość żyta, posmaki karmelowe, średnia goryczka i niesamowite słodkie drewno na finiszu, lekko cierpkie. Całość bardzo pijalna.

W aromacie cudowna beczkowa wanilia, która idealnie komponuje się z żytnią ziemisto - chlebową słodowością, super! W smaku podobnie, odczucie wanilii silne, jednak słabnie z każdym łykiem, na dodatek brakuje kontry goryczki (mizerna) lub zwiększonej pełni dla spotęgowania wrażenia. Niemniej jednak warto dla samego bajecznego aromatu. Do tego jest bardzo pijalne.
Z kranu w Targowej. Intensywny burbonowy aromat, s?odowo??, karmel. W smaku ponownie burbon, karmel, lekka pikantno?? i d?bina na j?zyku. Warto spróbowa?

Draught @ Fermentoren, Aarhus. Pours dark amber with a small offwhite head. Aroma of malt, rye, light sourness, bread, light fruit, oak, bourbon. Flavor is malt, rich caramel, cocoa, chocolate, vanilla, oak, bourbon. Medium body, soft carbonation, dry finish. 030915
25.4oz bottle from 2013. Cloudy reddish-brown hue. Overflowed on opening. Still tasted good, but the feathers got soaked. Nice rye/whiskey notes. Medium+ body and high carbonation.

Tap @ Fermentoren, Aarhus. Pours hazy brown/orange with a small white head. Aromas of rye, malt, caramel, ripe orange, vanilla, oak, dates, raisins, spice. Taste is bourbon, malt, vanilla, caramel, oak, raisins, dry woody finish.  ---Rated via Beer Buddy for Android

Pours clear chestnut with a very thick and frothy pale buff head. Aroma has caramel, malty, rye, and subtle bourbon and wood notes. Bourbon dominates the flavor, while letting rye, malt, and hints of caramel and hops to share the stage. Mouthfeel is the beers weakest point, thin and not very fizzy; however, it goes down well and pleases this here now beer lover. Dont be chiquen - grab a bottle and enjoy. Happy Birthday to Moi!

Cloudy brown color with a big head. The beer smells well the barrel aging. Apart that tart, cherries, yeasty dough. The carbonation is strong and the beers density is medium to thick. Flavor is dry and spicy with strong notes of (again) barrel aging. In that case alcohol is underlined with notes of bourbon and cherries. Bitterness is earthy and reminds a bit of clove. I really enjoy it to be honest.

on tap @ Party Town (Friday Night Flights) / Florence KY --- Cloudy dark amber color, ivory head, spots and dots of lace. Taste is caramel malt that has overtones of rye. Light carbonation on the swallow, finishing with mild hops. Chewy and full-bodied, lingers nicely. A solid brew.

Bottle 750ml @ Geokkjer
Pours slightly hazy amber with a off-white head. Aroma has notes of malt, caramel, vanilla, oak, alcohol and some fruitiness. Taste is medium sweet and light to medium bitter with a long slightly warm, vanilla, oak, caramel, slightly funky and fruity finish. Body is full, texture is oily, carbonation is soft.

Bottle, 75cl. An unclear, dark amber beer with almost no head. Off-white head. Gusher. Rather boozy nose with caramel and toffee, dried fruits, grassy, piney hops and some woody hints. Theres a nice carbonation level, its full-bodied and lightly warming, with some tannins. Semi-dry, nicely bittered and with peppery hints, toffee and dried fruits. Lasting dry and bitter finish with peppery malts, toffee and piney hops. Interesting, thats it. 150814

Bottle. Pours amber with an off-white head. Aroma of malt, some funk, slight citrus, some caramel and spices. Flavor is sweet and malt, with some funk, spices, some red apples and caramel. Medium body, average carbonation.

Bottle shared with BBGTC. Pours a clear brown amber with a offwhite top. Aroma is light malty with a slight floral touch, minerals and light toasted and woody malts. Tsste is balanced. Light sweet, dry and light bitter. Finishes dry with a lingering, light bitterness. Medium light body and avg co2.

Bottle, shared with BBGTC. Pours a light coppery brown-hued amber with a large off-white head. Nose is caramel, rye, grains, vanilla, bourbon and hints of red berries and baked bread. Taste is grains, vanilla, rye and hints of nuts and nougat. Light body, medium carbonation. A bit too watery, but fair enough.

Action packed beer! Reminded me of my first sexy-time, exploding prematurely upon opening! 

Well over carbonated! 

caramel pour with an escaping, light head. 
Nose has lots of malts and a hint of dry whisky. 

Smooth and easy drinkable, fruity caramel, light vanilla, whiskey finish. 

Jammy and dry.
Alcohol very understated but this ones a little boring otherwise. Pours maroon with OK head and lacing. Light bitter finish with some mash malt tang. Tap at GBD.
Pours a peachy yellow with a slight eggshell brown head. Aroma is mildly vinegar. Taste is smoked malts and mild baked apple.
Bottle thanks to Ian. Amber with off white head. Spicy aroma, wood, caramel. Taste of cinamon, spice, caramel. Little sweet. Nice
bottle at home .. daisy tasting ...soft swet toffee sweet malts ... light funky fruit nose ... soft malts ... soft frutis .. light swet tart sour fruits ... light funk
Bottle at Craigs tastingfruity whiskey, spicey, boozy, light. Amber, slick. Fruity

Bottle at Craigs. Cheers Iain! Gusher! Pours clear amber with a thin white head. Aromas of rye spice, whisky. Taste is boozy heat, spice, rye bread. Boozy finish. 

12th July, Daisy tasting

Pours reddish browm with a two finger tan head with excellent lacing. Aroma is of freshly baked rye bread, sweet malts, spearmint, light herbal notes,and some light whiskey notes. Taste is similar to the aroma but has woody oak, more whiskey flavor, and some light vanilla notes. Has a medium body with a semi crramy mouth feel and a semi dry, slightly bitter, medium-long finish. Overall, a pretty nice BA rye beer that isnt boozy like a lot of beer in the style.
Aroma is like fresh rye bread. Flavor is like pumpernickel with a bit of tang. Excellent body. Ditto appearance. Super drinkable.
Bottle pours clear tan, white billowing head. Rye in the nose. Taste is rye, slightly sweet. Minimal notion of barrell treatment. Medium body. Somewhat disappointing given the hype and ratings.

Thick, yellowish dense head, over clear chestnut beer, well-carbonated. Alcoholic, "hot" nose, liqueurish, some vanilla, and a very faint waft of patchouli, praliné chocolate, sweet. Dry, bitterish, leafy, and a faint but present Bourbon-like vanilla flavour in the back. Bit herbal finish. Very slick-oily, medium to well-bodied, alcoholwarming, well-carbonated feel. Nice, if a tad neutral.

shared bottle with a friend bought from an online web order. poured a dark amber to light brown colour. notes of sweet tofee, vanilla, caramel. oak, sweet sticky bourbon, dark red fruits, sherry, vineous notes, barley, smoke, spiced notes, not very well balanced.

750 ml Bottle. Pours a cloudy, coppery amber color topped with an inch of light reddish brown foam. Notes of fruity esters, brown sugar, tart fruit and toasted oak in the nose. The flavor is a blend of rye whiskey, caramel malt and raisins with a bit of sour funk around the edges. Mouthfeel is medium-bodied with Belgian Ale style strong carbonation and more rye and wood in the finish.

Bottle, a cool one! This one did explode! Pours slight cloudy amber with one finger beige cream head. Aroma is malty, caramel, strawberrie, yam, rye spice, whisky, slight toast, Taste is toasty malts, fruity, yam, caramel strawberrie, nice whisky booze. Bit thin body with low carbonation, probably because of the explosion, quite a shame. Dry whisky finish. Well balanced.

Bottle @Fermenteam tasting! Huge gush! Pours a Nice, dark, clear, reddish amber, off White head. Aroma has sweet rye whiskey, slight vanilla, slight booze, slight Dark fruits with a hint of tartness. Lots of rye. Seems very dry. Taste is sweet and dry, slight jammy fruityness. Not the thickest body actually, but the dry rye finish and the carbonation adds a different but still balanced attitude.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
23 Apr 2015, bottle. orange. nose is sweet smarties candy. med/thin body and mildly fizzy. smarties candy, slightly acidic, rye in the background. men.
This poured a lighter brown with a beige head. Aroma was of whiskey, vanilla, caramel and toasted malt. Flavor was similar, but heading towards lighlt barrel sour Ans falling into infection.

draft sampler this was the barrel aged version. and it poured a medium yellow with white head. appeared to be whiskey barrels, but I could be wrong. got the rye spice in the nose and in the flavor and that oaky woody barrel taste. thought this would be different but its not...I dont know but just wasnt a fan of this one.
Bottle - Sweet caramel and rye with some oak. Clearish gold with a decent white head. Sweet caramel, light bitter hops and more rye sweetness.
(750ml bottle) rye, light alcohol, celery, plastic, weird palate linger, spices and a slick palate. Odd beer.

Bottle with the feathers (750ml): Pours light brown with a beige head. Plenty of gushing going on after I opened this one. Aroma is light notes of vanilla, a strange kind of rye that stands out as rye, but very unlike the way it manifests itself elsewhere (is there even rye in this or is it just aged in whiskey barrels... I dont know), plus some distinct fruitiness, light funk, and vanilla, Taste is something akin to a sour. Nice malty backbone. Understated frutiiness. Plenty of wood. Interesting and complex. Not at all what I was expecting.

I wish our bottle had feathers! :) it just said cluck cluck cluck on top.
Anywho, this amber ale is pretty barrel dominated. Lots of booze and rye, as the beer is maybe not quite strong enough to stand up to the barrels. Pleasant, just not very deep as you get whiskey, rye and a hint of sweet malt. little to no hop presence. Not bad, but overpriced.

10 oz at Asbury. Pours cloudy dark amber with a small head. Aroma is more estery than expected with notes of banana. Rye is prominent with supporting hints of vanilla. The palate is not as full as I thought it would be. I get hints of cinnamon in the flavor with rye, oak, banana and caramel. You tell me Im gonna drink a rye beer thats over 8% and aged in bourbon barrels, I envision something different than this. Not that this is unpleasant at all. It aight.

On Draught
Pours a hazy rust color with a small head and decent lacing on the glass.

The aroma is odd... sorta sweet tart like with some oak. Its got a lot of whiskey and sweet malt....... in a sort of good way.

The flavor is practically the same as the aroma more sweet tarts, oak and vanilla. Its kind of boozy, its not overly sweet... 

huh, its not bad... but man, Im not sure its great either...............

Brown color with a light beige head with medium lasting. Aroma has notes of caramel, some yeast ans strong rye notes. Flavor with a lot of spices: jinger and vanilla hints, some caramel and s high presence of rye. Mild bittery in the final with toasted mouthfeel.
A different beer that came across more like a sour than a rye. Would love to have this beer beside Blvd. Love Child #4...I think they are very similar.

Pour out of 750 mL bottle, hazy dark reddish pour with white head, aroma brought notes of grain, bread, caramel, toffee, hints of slight barrel and oak notes, touch of earthy spice. Taste was a mix of bread, caramel, toffee, some yeast, some slight oak, rye, belgian yeast, finishing sweet, slightly dry. Eh.
On tap at 800 degrees pours a dark brown with a small off white head. Banana roasted malt and slight rye taste.

750. No feathers. Thanks, J! Pours a murky dark amber with a dense and creamy tan head that goes away right away. Big funky wet-grain nose, doesnt smell as appetizing as it turns out to taste. Creamy thick body, almost sticky. Soft carb. Big heavy darkly toasted caramel mid palate, with apricots and vanilla knocking around. Heavy, semi-sweet finish.

Bottle shared by Jacob at the meeting tonight, thanks for the opportunity!
Spicy rye with a hint of maltiness. Light spirit flavor and heat. Decent drinker, but I wanted more body or sweetness to play off the spiciness of this brew.
Tap at orsted olbar. Dark amber color, tanned head. Sweet aroma, raisin, plums. Sweet malty taste, corn, raisins.

Hazy orange thick off white head. Slight vanilla rye aroma. Sweet smooth and malty. Hints of oak and brown sugar

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This draft brew from a restaurant poured a extremely small sized head of foamy finely sized white colored bubbles that were fully diminished and left behind a no visible carbonation semi-opaque light orange brown colored body and a poor lacing. The almost non-existent aroma was malty. The semi-dry crisp mouth feel was very tingly at the start and at the finish with a mellow hoppy aftertaste. The balanced flavor contained notes of rye wood mild nut mild hops and crisp. An OK brew just nothing special.
on tap bel ramato buona schiuma persistenza buona nota maltata lieve legno note acidule vaniglia discreto amaro erbaceo un po terroso

Appearance is red with bone head. Flavor is right on the nose; though the bourbon shines through more than the rye malts, imo. The finish is slightly resiny a little booze. Palate is bubbly with slight liveliness.
Keg at Beer Temple. Pours deep brown, nose is toffee, vanilla, woody, taste is similar, light spice.

Bottle... Pours clear and Longhorn-orange with a small, fizzy, white head that dissipates faster than you can say "quick!" The aroma is a mishmash of rye grain, rye whisky and mellow notes of oaken barrel, sticky caramel and tea biscuit. Full-bodied with a fatty mouthfeel and moderate carbonation. The flavor is a boozy, malty marriage of caramel and a rye-whiskey barrel offering notes of grainy rye and black tea instead of overbearing alcohol heat. This is very enjoyable, but not mind-bending. The bottle is the ugliest thing Ive seen in quite a while. Fun stuff. Bottle courtesy of StFun!

750 ml bottle into snifter, no bottle dating. Pours slightly hazy dark orange/copper color with a 1-2 finger fairly dense light khaki head with good retention, that reduces to a small cap that lingers. Nice dense soapy lacing clings around the glass, with a large amount of streaming carbonation retaining the head. Aromas of caramel, toast, toffee, brown bread, vanilla, brown sugar, light nuttiness, raisin, plum, fig, apple, bourbon, oak, herbal, light pepper, and yeast/oak earthiness. Very nice aromas with good balance and complexity of dark/bready malt, oak barrel, and yeast ester notes; with good strength. Taste of caramel, toast, toffee, brown bread, brown sugar, vanilla, light nuttiness, raisin, plum, fig, apple, bourbon, oak, herbal, light pepper, and yeast/oak earthiness. Light earthy/spicy bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of caramel, toast, toffee, brown bread, brown sugar, raisin, plum, fig, apple, bourbon, oak, herbal, light pepper, and yeast/oak earthiness on the finish for a while. Very nice complexity, balance, and robustness of dark/bready malt, oak barrel, and yeast ester flavors; with a good malt/bitterness balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a smooth, moderately crisp, and fairly creamy/bready mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with only a slight warming present after the finish. Overall this is a damn nice English strong ale. All around great complexity and balance of dark/bready malt, oak barrel, and yeast ester flavors; and very smooth to sip on for the ABV. A very enjoyable offering.

Bottle shared with Simonsen and Carsten
A slow gusher from an interesting looking bottle full of chicken feathers, i think its a cool idea. Pours copper clear with a frothy white head. Smell of dark fruity malt malts, spicy rye, quite malt driven for sure, some oak and booze in the back. Moderate to medium sweet, malty, fruity, some oak and vanilla, booze. Quite interesting taste, itsgot just a bit of that barrel aging character without blowing the original malt flavors away. Nice
nice rye aroma,amber, cloudy, off white foam, light sweetness, lightly bitter, realy nice fat vanilla rye finish.

On tap @ Uber. Pours golden brown with thin lacy head, off-white in color. Aroma is big crisp sharply fruity sweet malt. Taste is similar; the rye body quickly overwhelms the sweetness in a somewhat balanced finish, and the heavy rye keeps things from getting too sweet. Quite bitter from all the rye here. This is a weird beer, I liked it though.

@Cimmeria, Oviedo. Nice bottle with feathers, hard to pour without getting feather in the glass. Sweet aroma, fruity and faint vanilla. Faint sherry too. Just let rest a bit in the glass. Creamy texture and soft carbonation.

On tap at Ørsted, Mash Up II. Pours a clear amber with an off white, foamy head and lacings. Sweet with light aromas of dark sugars. Tiny bourbon hints. Medium bodied. Medium carbonation. Light dry finish. Boring.

Botella de 75cl en cimmeria en el momento el 12-09-2014. Color ámbar algo oscuro y bastante turbio con poca espuma beige claro. Aromas y sabores de cereales y centeno este ultimo no muy intenso seguido de tonos dulces ( que aumentan según va calentando) de maderas empapadas en whiskey tampoco muy intensos. Final ligeramente amargo. Todo bastante equilibrado y sin sobresaltos. Redonda y original.

Tap at Irreale. Cloudy red-orange, low creamy head. Very light grain nose. Mellow mouthfeel, medium body. Nutty entry, turron, rye/barrel notes, grassy hops, light cookie aftertaste. I was thankful it did not have too much rye whisky going on, but it felt a bit too subdued - maybe because it was the end of the barrel?
Caoba oscuro con espuma marfil. Aroma dulce, miel, ligero toque de limón. Cuerpo meido-bajo, textura maltosa. Inicio dulce con final bastante seco. bien.
Tap. Sweet, fruity aroma. Yeasty, fermented bread and woody taste. Deep, dry barrel notes. Oily body with red vinuous character.

750ml bottle @Cimmeria, Oviedo. 05-09-2014.
BBD: not found.
In short: spicy ale.
Pours clear amber with little off white head. Short head retention, some lacing. Caramel, fruity, liquor aromas. Medium body, soft carbonation, oily texture. Taste is caramel, ripe fruit, spicy, some liquor notes. Warming aftertaste. Enjoyable.
On tap at Biercab. Brown colour with off-white head. Disgusting seafood and carnic aroma. Caramel and malt taste. Medium body.

Dunkel getrediger Antrunk, weich. Harmonisch, das Bier bleibt dunkel und wirdhefiger, zwischenzeitlich hat es Ähnlichkeiten mit einem Weizenbock. Deutlich hefig, milde hintergründige aber beständige Whiskeynoten. Im Mittelteil ist ein passender dezenter Alkoholtouch vorhanden. Gut! 8/12/12/10/8/12
Cloudy amber-brown. Sweet nose, alcohol, light banana, toasty malts, alcohol, hint of barrel. Ok, but ultimately doesnt come together.
Bottle. Pours orange with white head. Aroma is fruity, tropical, cherry, wild, strawberry. Taste is wild, dry, light, spicy....Meh.

Serving: 750 ml. bottle. Deep, ruddy pour with a small, light tan head. Bready nose with a little bubble gum and Belgian yeast. Spiced bread, rye whiskey, light caramel, and bubble gum. Comes across as more alcoholic than it is.

Pours a rusty amber color with two fingers of eggshell foam. The nose is pretty straight forward with some bready caramel, spicy whisky and rustic grain. Palate follows the nose but the barrel flavors are well subdued and the beer just taste a bit lifeless. Still not a bad beer just nothing that excited the palate. Spicy earth from the rye mingles nicely with the sweet toffee, vanilla and bourbon nuttiness.
Taster at ei8ht ball - nose is BA. Sip adds vanilla and wood. Wow. Just wow. Surpassed my expectations by a gill. Party beer.

6 oz. pour at Farmhouse Tap & Grill. Hazy amber color with very little head retention. Aroma is weak rye and weak bourbon. The flavor is mild rye, weak caramel and a note of astringent sour oak. The biggest flavor is the whisky / bourbon notes. In fact it is mostly bourbon with the other flavors being subdued by it. But the bourbon character is also weak. The body is thin and watery. Major let down here and this was a draft sample. Yeah, glad I didnt buy a bottle.

Thanks to errl for sharing this bottle. While the recent reviews are positive, the bottle we had was definitely off. Pours and amber color with a white head. The aroma has some oak and rye notes, but there is also a strong presence of plastic. The flavor is a bit better, but still not up to what other reviews say it is/should be. There is some tobacco and toffee character, but the plastic and dirt are also present. Medium mouthfeel and medium carbonation.

Clear deep amber under a thin ring of foam that lasts. Lovely nose of sweet toffee malts and caramelly whiskey with some oak tones and bready rye. Smooth and complex flavor of rye dough, caramel, whiskey, oak, a light tone of char, and nutty sweet malts. The rye whiskey tone is smooth and sweet and delightful, not overbearing. Wonderful.
Draft pour. Pours a clear copper with no head. The aroma has big smoke and booze. Some caramel and toffee notes as well. The taste is heavy on the booze profile. Sticky mouthfeel. Low carbonation.
Poured from the tap. Murky dark red brown with very minimal white head. Rye, caramel, and alcohol flavour.

On draught during Baileys Taprooms Seventh Anniversary Barrel-Aged BeerFest. Caramel amber color. Aroma is sweet caramel apple, rye, and hard candies. Taste is similar to aroma, with some bitter toffee notes. A little too sweet, but some nice rye notes.
Slight haze to this toffee colored pour. Big light tan head. Lacing. Peppery malt aroma. Some caramel and vanilla. Carbonic caramel flavor. Dry.
Bottle share at Tribes Alehouse. Pour is dark amber/brown with a small off-white head. Aroma and flavor of rye bread, whiskey, earth, spice, and dark fruit. Dry and earthy.
Flaske medbrakt av esp0r. Klar kobberfarget, hvit skumtopp, moderat karbonert. Smaker fotsvette, dansk ost, malt, karamell, krydder og noe fruktig

This is a really murky beer, muddy brown in color with a light brown head. Yeah, it looks muddy. It has a murky, muddy, malty thickness and a little sourness in the nose that reminds me of sourdough. The flavor introduces you a little deeper, with caramel, yeast, rye, and a touch of bourbon. Its dense and chewy, and a sour, rye quality rounds out the finish. Theres some nice fruit notes in this with a big mouthful and a tarty sourness in the finish. My cheeks are puckering. Its a powerful beer. I expected the body to be the hardest thing to stomach, but its more the flavor. Still, this is a pretty impressive beer. And I do like the feathers.

Bottle @ RBSG 2014 Grand Tasting. The first beer Ive ever had with chicken feathers on the bottle. Dark amber pour with a small off-white head. Minimal whiskey/barrel, but some sweet caramel and some toffee. Light smoke, charred wood, and prunes. Flavor has a decent sweetness of caramel, toffee, and dark fruits. Slight bitter and chalkiness of charred oak. Some chocolate, prune, and mild whiskey. Not bad.

750 ml bottle. Served in a Great Lakes Brewing chalice, the beer pours a hazy ruby red/brown color with about an inch off-white head. Head retention is good, and theres a decent amount of lacing. Aroma is nice, the brew smells like caramel, rye bread, rye whiskey, and some dark fruit. It tastes like spicy rye, rye whiskey, caramel, dark fruit, wood, and some earthiness. Its mostly a sweet, malty tasting brew, but theres also a good amount of bitterness. Mouthfeel/body is medium/full, its a bit coating with low/moderate carbonation. I liked this brew, I wouldnt mind picking up a bottle of this again soon. $12.00 a bottle purchased at the brewpub.
Dark red brown pour clear. Aroma caramel slight roast super malt. Tastes grape spicy grain slight creamy tannins. woody slight choc.
Interesting feathered bottle pour. Pours copper with a malty, caramel aroma. A lot of rye in this one. Nutty flavor with a malty, bitter

Gimmick bottle where I left all those feathers on the floor at the store... stupid! Anyways about the brew itself, pours a nice ruby hue with a fading head, not much lace. Lots of rye overtones and whiskey, caramel and grassy notes. A little bit of banana bread, prune, and some charred oak. Tasty but I was hoping for something more dynamic. That said the use of rye was well done.

On tap at BtlRev (Raleigh). 

Pours a reddish brown (pretty red) with a touch of head. Creamy aroma - reminds me of the aroma of Creme Brûlée. But there's also a noticeable touch of rye in the aroma...

Taste is sweet cream complemented with the rye. Not disturbingly sweet like Creme Brûlée as the rye partially cuts through the sweetness. 

This is a dessert beer. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

2/28/14. On tap at the brewery. Amber red pour with a nice khaki head. Nice aroma, plenty of whiskey pops through, bits of oak, vanilla, caramel, and a touch of spicy bread. Nice flavor, sweet whiskey complements the nice malt base with a touch of spice. Nice.

Brewdog levels of bottle gimmickery aside, the beer pours a hazy reddish-brown color with a medium light beige head that diminishes steadily. Partial rings of lacing. Aroma of rye whisky, fruit and malt. Medium-bodied with flavors of spicy rye, booze, caramel malt and ripe fruit. The finish is oaky vanilla and spiced rye. Above average overall.
Draft. Rich amber beer with a dark cream head. Bourbon aroma. Bourbon and light caramel flavor with light butter. Medium bodied. Bourbon and light vanilla lingers with light butter and caramel.

Bottle from Healthy Spirits. Pours murky orange copper with a tiny beige head and a grain and fruit aroma. There is a medium-bodied rye and whiskey flavor that is neither sweet nor bitter but pretty mellow. This is a unique brew that is fun to drink. However, I am happy to get the nasty chicken feathers out of my fridge.

Capped 750 shared by Marcus. Pours ruddy copper with an of-white head. Aromas of rye spice, brown sugar and oak. Full bodied. Flavor is very rye. Wood is mild. Lots of treacle. Yet its not sweet. Mildly bitter. Very different and very tasty.
Odd feathered bottle. Pours a clear copper color with a small white head. A sweet banana ester nose, some caramel and barrel. The flavor is hot funky bananas, earthy, toffee, caramel. Pretty good.
Échantillonné du Extreme beer fest 2014: Se boit comme une amber ale assez résineuse mais un touche plus épicée et poivrée. Le vieillissement en rye barrel est pas trop exubérant, solide liquide.

A good beer for me. Probably a great beer if you are a lover of the distilled rye. Definitely the prominent flavour for me. Like a decent english ale that someone spiked with whisky. Not my favorite, but still well done. Had on tap at Edmunds oast. Looks like a really nice pale ale but nose and taste are almost as much spirit as ale. Interesting.
On tap at apex. Slightly hazy rose/amber, steady white cap. Aroma of rye, wood, moist sock, floral notes, malt. Taste is sweet and tart. Medium carbonation, dry finish. Quite interesting.

On tap at Delirium Hoppy Loft. 
Nose: vanilla, whisky barrel. 
Taste: this is very special. The first taste is quite a hard hit of spicy rye. Then lots of sweet and sticky vanilla. Incredibly smooth, velvety mouth feel.
Very interesting beer to taste, especially for a whisky lover, though not something to drink every day.

Draft @ Hoppy Loft.
Ambrée, col blanc cassé épais.
Arôme offre de suite de très belles effluves de Bourbon sur un boisé subtil.
Le houblon est caché apportant très peu en terme de caractère olfactif. 
Palais de barrique, super, douceur vanillée résiduelle, pointe amer de houblons sur un fini primant sur la douceur. Caramel léger avec un ajout seigle donnant qcq notes épicées. Amertume reste en retrait par rapport à une bière qui prime tout de même sur le Bourbon.

Au final, une très belle bière, malheureusement servie bcp trop froide (mais bon cest Délirium, faut pas trop demander). Une fois à t° ambiante, le profil et le caractère souvrent, mettant à profit toute la complexité du BA.
Flavors of vanilla, caramel, and some very slight tartness and hints of marshmallow. Light bodied, and pretty good amount of flavor for its lightness.

Bottle, 8.6 abv. Light hazy reddish brown, medium sized diminishing head. Marzipan, caramel, coconut, oak, dried fruits, tannins, light alcohol. Medium body, oily texture, soft carbonation, medium sweet. I like it, but the tannins are a bit much. After a bit getting used to, I like it more and more.

Bottle. I really only gave this a second look because of the feathers on the bottle. Glad I did. The spice from the rye is the main thing in the aroma and the flavor. Spicy rye up front, then a bit of malt sweetness that leads you to a dry rye finish. wish I had more of this.

(bottle - 750 ml) Chicken feathers on the bottle makes it a lot more hilarious than a beer usually is. Slightly cloudy copper pour. Sweet wood notes and a lot of dry rye in the finish with a light malty note. The rye barrels really come through at the start of the flavor. Dry malts from the beer itself are lifted up from the vanilla and wood of the barrel. The rye dryness really comes up at the end.

Bottle at RBWG grand tasting 
Cloudy amber with a medium sized off-white head and some lacing. Aroma of toasted malts and maple. Flavors of roasted malts, maple and brown sugar 
Decent
Bottle pour. Just flat out amazing! Smooth, silky, carmel notes with an insane rye bourbon finish. Best beer of the year so far!

On tap. Murky dark copper color with coarse off white head. Aroma of bourbon, vanilla, sweet wood notes, perfume and spicy notes. Taste is herby, medium sweet, vanilla, alcohol, vanilla and spice. Sweet and heavy body.
RBWG14 Trip Rating #132. Bottle shared at the Grand Tasting. Aroma of chocolate, rye, stone fruit, earth. Taste is caramel malt, stone fruit, rye whiskey. Medium bodied.

Bottle shared at RBWG grand tasting! Pours a slightly hazy golden brown with fluffy tan head that dissipates to leave light lace. Aroma is all bourbon barrel. Taste is a bit more of the malt and rye spice, nice flavor. Very nicely done, but the bottle is a bit of a gimmick.

Bottle thanks to Jeff for sharing. Pours a cloudy amber color with a small foamy head that slowly fades to a ring. Aromas are oak, caramel, citrus and rye whiskey. Taste has a strong oak presence throughout. Some underlying citrus and caramel mix with the strong barrel taste. Touch of booziness in the finish. Decent beer but I dont think the base beer was strong enough for barrel treatment.

Courtesy of northernbrews
Bottle: The aroma consists of caramel, toffee, rye, citrus, alcohol, and whiskey. It pours a slightly hazy reddish-orange with a small khaki head that quickly fades to a thin ring. The flavor starts with a quick dose of caramel, toffee, and faint fruit. The finish has oxidation, rye, and light whiskey. Its medium bodied with mild carbonation.
Bottle pour dark copper. Nose whiskey and sweet malt, some spice. Taste sweet up front, Mild whiskey. Sweet and spice on finish.

The pours light amber with a small head. The aromas of toffee, toasted grain, sweet apple sauce. Spiced cake. Mild damson and plum. The taste is boozy raisin, treacle. Some vanilla. Fruit by the foot candy. Spicy. Pretty light body, aggressively carbed. Overall, not bad.

750ml bottle. Pours a dark amber red color with a small off white head. Aroma of whiskey, rye, mild red fruit notes. Lots of earth, dirt, and woods notes. Flavor is dry, earthy, lots of rye and whiskey notes. Medium bodied, somewhat creamy mouthfeel, soft carbonation. This is interesting, but ultimately not particularly impressive.

Shared 750 ml. bottle poured to snifters after a brief photo session. Actually, quite clear & bright, with a copper color, off white head that diminished to a bubbly ring & light film, and spots of clingy lacing. The aroma was a little nondescript, with whiskey & light barrel presence, a touch of spiciness, and some almond extract. Medium bodied, with soft carbonation, as some light esters joined the aroma notes, the alcohol showed a little warmth, and there was a pleasant dryness to the finish. Nice fanfare with the feathers & graphics, basically decent, but unremarkable.
Nice offering. Barrell flavor adds alot and really comes through in the flavor.
Overall great beer in this style category. Solid all across the board and would get every time.

750ml bottle pours a hazy brown with some creamy, off white head. Nose is dusty, orange, malt, blood orange, soap, herbs, some booze. Flavor is malty, sweet, brown sugar, carrots, booze, mild wood. Clean finish. Not a ton of barrel.

31-DEC-2013, bottle @Morten.
Aroma is rye bread and weak Bourbon. Taste the same with caramel, spice. A lot more Bourbon in the taste. Fine but strange.
Amber colour. Smells of sweet bourbon. Taste is malty with lots of bourbon.
redish color,light body. poor aromas. malty taste wit a huge bourbone aftertaste. nice beer but not for every day

750ml bottle in a shaker. Pours amber with a lacy, off-white head. Aroma of rye whiskey, some caramel and pale malts, a little rye spiciness, light dough, and some light, floral hops. Flavor the same. Average texture. Not a bad beer.

Tap. Pours hazy, deep amber with a small off-white head.Aroma of caramel, rye and bourbon notes. Sqeet flavor that ends up more dry and with bitter notes. Medium bodied, oily texture and soft carb. An interesting and quite nice amber.

Copper pour tall thick white head well laced. Rye whiskey aroma light pepper not much else. Full well coated palate. Flavor is sweet butter and caramel light whiskey in the finish. very rich lots of butter. Pretty good

Pours to a rusty brown body with a super creamy white head. Aroma is heavily rye with lots of oak barrel and rye alcohol. The flavor is deliciously rye all the way through. Some vanilla and coconut. Chocolate. Extremely easy drinking.

Thanks to Blake and Jenny for bringing it! Poured medium reddish-amber with a short toasted beige head. The aroma picked up lots of rye plus coconut and licorice.. lots of sweet nondescript undertones. The flavor found lots of coconut and rye.. slightly tart edges with oak and whiskey leading.. finished with a lot of barrel and a lot of warmth. Medium-bodied and rye-y.. ok feel and flow.. solid.

750ml, feathered covered (yes feathers) bottle. Poured an amber color with an off white head. Aromas of rye, bourbon, wood, and some caramel. Tastes of vanilla, bourbon, wood, and rye. I found this one to be quite drinkable if somewhat thinner body.

UPDATED: SEP 10, 2014 Bottle: thanks, Tim! Nice bottle with the feathers... be careful not to drop into your beer, though. Mildly cloudy, deep copper body with a gray tinted film on top that sifts slowly into a lazy collar. Aroma is light toast, dry rye, light plum & grape sweetness, & a staunch, boozy character. Kind of like a "stale" barleywine with a bit of rye... Not really doing it for me. Taste is sharp & full of toasted bread loaves, a heap of rye, oak, & a slightly sweet, fruitiness in the finish. Actual fruit is hard to pinpoint, but its along the lines of fig or grape. Slight booziness & oak takes over in the aftertaste. An okay brew, but nothing to write home about.

Bottle: (with plumage)
Pours cloudy, medium brown with a small, light tan head.
Rye malt aroma.
Taste is sweet....toffee...rye malt, bread.
Very nice, subdued barrel notes.
A little sticky booziness.
Very good.
Bottle. Clear amber put with an off white head. Barrel aromas. Mild rye and spice notes. Average body and mouthfeel.
Tap @ Beertemple, medium sample. Hazy orange color, short head. Aroma of rye, bourbon, caramel. Bit sweet, bit bitter, cookie. Nice

Weird, crazy bottle shared by Ed, thanks a bunch dude. Pours out a brownish to dark amber color with a small white head. Aroma is of watered down grain whiskey, caramel and some light toffee, o and some rye notes. Taste is much the same, body is a little thin, watered down rye whiskey, light caramel, toffee and some grainy notes in there as well. Gets some more overall points for the name and the bottle for an otherwise solid,but nothing memorable beer.

Bottle shared at Sante Adairius, thanks Jason! This is basically chocolate milk. Something about the rye malt always evokes that for me. Dry but full-flavored, nice modest ABV, something you can drink forever.

Draft to taster. Looks good; a mostly transparent orangish brown with white lacing. Smells of bourbon, oak, and mild rye spice. Tastes like it smells, only more robust, and with some vanilla too. Nice and smooth on the palate. Enjoyable, and drinks significantly better than it smells.
Draft at Beer Temple. Pours heavy hazy amber with a moderate of white head. Aroma of rye, caramel, vanilla/bourbon. Flavour is over moderate sweet and bitter. Medium bodied with soft carbonation.

Draft at the Beer Temple. pours meiumbroown with nice head. Nose is mild notesof bourbon, vanilla, brown malt and rye. First sip is sweet with bourbon followed by a strong but not over powering rye. finish is smooth with a clean finish
Bottle thanks to phaleslu. Middle name "So Chill." Moose full of sweetness. Not much barrel. Taste is similar. Kinda bland. Missing the hops and barrel. Slightly spivey but thats about it.

On tap at Beer Temple! Pours a near clear amber orange with a tan head that dissipates to the edges. Aroma has a good amount of rye with a grouch of sweetness and strong bourbon barrel. Backing. Flavor has a nice rye note throughout that is more balanced by the barrel.
On tap at Beer Temple. Hazy copper brown, small head. Sweet rummy aroma, hints of oranges. The flavours are on the sweet side, but not excessively so. Hoped for more.

On tap at Beer Temple. Clear amber colour, off-white head. Aroma of bourbon, vanilla, oak, caramel/toffee, fudge, light floral. Flavour is medium-sweet, malty, caramel, bourbon, rye bitterness, harsh and sharp alcohol-bite in the finish. Medium-bodied. OK.

750ml bottle covered in feathers thanks to drfabulous. Thanks Jeff! Pours a hazy dark amber color with a thin off white head. Aroma of spicy rye malt, caramel, and whiskey. Mouthfeel is a little thin. Taste of spices, rye malt, earth, toasted malt, and whiskey.

Cool ass feathered up bottle shared by my doge Ed5388. Poured an ugly medium density mud brown with a nice smaller foamy off white head. Aroma is very woody, whiskey, dry vanilla and a hint of chocolate. Medium bodied with average carbonation dry alcohol finish. Flavor of chocolate, whiskey, dry wood, dry vanilla, old toffee and butter. Despite the driness I sort of liked it at first but then this one sort of got away from me and I started thinking meh.

750ml feathered bottle, shared by beerpig317. Mostly hazy amber orange red color. Minimal off-white head, a few loose bits of lace. Spicy rye in the nose, with a hint of whiskey. Nice caramel malt, sort of toasty spicy rye malt aroma, with a hint of chocolate. Medium to bigger body. Very light carbonation. Lightly sticky body, but more dry finish. Nice bourbon character to the rye malts, and a light spicy fruity hop dancing around with it all. Taste is big bitter and spicyness, light sweet in the finish, with a light warmth, too. Good smooth, mellow finish. Very nice complex rye beer. Whiskey is not overpowering.

Draught @ CBC2013. Pours clear reddish brown with a rather small frothy off-white head that leaves some trace and lacing on the glass while dissipating. Smell is sweet and malty with sweet dark bread, black pepper corns, dry wood, bourbon, vanilla fudge, toffee, pumpernickel bread, roasted nuts, hay and hints of alcohol. Taste is tiny sweet, slightly bitter and malty with toasted malts, pumpernickel bread, vanilla fudge, toffee, bourbon, charred wood, vanilla fudge, coconut milk, roasted nuts, grass, resinous pine cones, dark grapes and lemon zest. Mouthfeel is round, tiny dry, tiny boozy and medium bodied. Finish is bitter and malty with pumpernickel bread, charred wood, vanilla fudge, bourbon, hay and resinous pine cones.

Sampled at Kennys. Thanks Shep. Clear and whiskey looking. Tons of rye grain in this. It gives a spicy flavor but the spice is more complex. Very light hops add character. Plenty of malts. Good stuff.

Bottle thanks to Bruce at the Pre-Zwanze. It pours deep brown with a small white head. The nose is roasty, toast, meaty, vanilla, wood and rye bread. The taste is toast, spice, rye, juicy fruits, alcohol, toffee and wood with a dry, sweetish finish. Medium body and fine carbonation. Pretty drinkable stuff.

Pours a dark slightly hazy amber with a white head that quickly dissipates. Aromas of earthy rye and oak with almost a buttery whiskey aroma to it. Really interesting. Flavor is smooth oaky rye with light carbonation. Buttery toffee notes in the finish. Very tasty.

Draught. Creamy white good mostly lasting head. Dark yellow colour. Moderate malty and hoppy aroma. Moderate bitter flavor. Streng vanilla aroma. Bourbon cask? Average moderate bitter finish. Creamy palate.

Bottle courtesy of clocks shared at Zwanze 2013. Pours a light, clear amber body with thin off white lacing. Aroma is rubber, molasses and maple. Mouthfeel is thin with sugar caramel flavors and light maple.
Bottle with feathers. Brown pour with tan head. Rye, oak and sweet aromas. Aroma would have you believe in a more intense flavor, but its more mild, plenty of rye. Very different.
Bottle. Pours reddish brown. Off white head. Nose and taste of rye, oak, vanilla coke, vanilla, caramel and toast. Medium body.
Bottle at pre zwanze tasting. Thanks to Bruce. Aroma is weird salted nuts sweet caramel. Some vanilla and slight booze. Rye is spicy.

UPDATED: NOV 5, 2013 Bottle at the Pre-Zwanze tasting - London. Many thanks to Bruce. Epic bottle. Feathers. Pours clear, amber-ruby with a fine, creamy head. Nose has some tropical fruits, orange. Medium sweet flavor, some bready malts, a bit of toffee, marmalade, alcohol. Medium to full bodied with fine to average carbonation. Sweet finish with lightly toasted malts, some citrus fruits, berries. Very tasty beer. Well balanced. (4.0)Sampled at Copenhagen Beer Celebration 2013 - Day 2, Session 2. Pours clear, copper-red with a fine, tan cream head. Has a nose of ripe, well aged fruits, berries and golden raisins. Big sweet flavor with more ripe fruits, light toffee, dates, golden raisins, faint dry bread. Full bodied with fine carbonation. Lightly warming to finish with sticky fruit sugars, dates, rich bread. Decent balance to this fella. Good one. (4.1)
Amber with a white head - Nice malt and hop aroma with some wood - Taste is of malt with a lot of wood and vanilla in the back - some of the vanilla continues into the finfish - this was quite good

On tap at the GTMW 2013

Another winning release from the masters at Against the Grain this one is so popular that it still is being sold at the brewpub. The right balance of barrel aging and base beer has created a deceptively drinkable masterpiece.

Aroma / Appearance - A rich creamy base looks as thick and dense as it should be from the description. Rye, malt, and oak strike the senses but the booziness, while evident, is never over the top.

Flavor / Palate - Rye and oak warm the palate after just a single sip. A chewy mouthfeel then starts to carry its payload to a bitter warm finish. Sticky as if drinking melted cheese it hangs in the throat. This is a top notch barrel aged project and worth trying if it is ever bottled.

On tap at GTMW 2013 - Pours deep amber with a light tan head. Nose is real malty with a little grassy hops and lightly spicy rye. Taste is lots of sweet bready malt, light grassy/herbal hops. Dont really get much barrel character. Medium-bodied and well-carbonated. Just not all that good.

Draught @ CBC 2013 [ Blue Session ]. - Copenhagen Beer Celebration 2013, Sparta Hallen, Gunnar Nu Hansens Plads 11, 2100 Copenhagen, DenmarkUnclear medium orange colour with a average, frothy, good lacing, mostly lasting, off-white head. Aroma is moderate malty, caramel, nutty, oat - rye, moldy - fusty. Flavour is moderate sweet and light to moderate bitter with a long duration, keller, caramel. Body is medium, texture is oily, carbonation is soft. [20130504]

Draft pour at GTMW 2013. Great name. Nice people. Ill be visiting here soon. This beer pours a mostly clear amber color with a small off-white head that spots the glass. Bourbon is very much present, with vanilla, caramel, oak, rye, and dried fruits. Light-medium bodied, with a malty, sweet, dry mouthfeel and moderate carbonation. Unusual beer that I enjoyed.
On tap at against the grain brewery Strong barrel aroma with a great burbon and rye flavor, oak seems to come through as well! Really good

on tap at mikkeller and friends. rich dark amber with a light haze and a steady head; aroma hints at rye, lightly bready with a whiff of apple schnapps; notes of caramel and vanilla but finishes reasonably dry. pretty drinkable
Nice complex beer with rye notes and a fair amount of barrel, not too sweet.

Poured a deep reddish brown with a frothy beige head. Aroma of wood and vanilla over sweet bourbon with some sweet dark fruit. Full body, flavour as the aroma, well balanced, some roasting coming through.

On tap at Mikkeller & Friens. Hazy amber with a decent off white head. Boozy nose of bourbon, oak, raisins. Very sweet flavor, malty, herbal, bready, vanilla spiced with lots of rye and notes of ripe fruits. Smooth, almost creamy texture. Dry finish.

On tap. Pours hazy amber with a medium off white head. The aroma is malty and herbal with bread and light vanilla notes. Flavor is light bourbon, malt, floral hops and ripe fruit. Nice!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On tap @ In De Wildeman (advertised as 8.6%!). Brown-red color, clear. Soapy, off white head, with good lacing. Aromas: oak, bourbon, vanilla, with some sweetness retronasal. Flavor is light sweet, bourbon, oak, vanilla. Medium bodied. Finishes light bitter and woody. At first this so-so, but it gets better and better as the glass gets emptier with the aromas and flavors seemingly getting more and more balanced. Nice overall.

Draft at Mikkeller & Friends. Pours hazy dark amber. Aroma is ripe apple, caramel, orange, hay. Taste is ripe apple, caramel, brandy, hay, orange, peach. Very well balanced!

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
CBC 2013. Pours clear red mahogany with a small off white head. Aroma is fruity earthy a bit sweet almonds. Flavor is as aroma, nice bitterness a bit dry.
Draft, pours dark amber with white head. Aroma is malty with a aged note to it. Flavours malty with caramel and bread, bassin and other store fruity.
Draft at the Festival. Hazy amber color, white head. Aroma of pine and light spices. Taste is floral pine resin, spice. Nice.

UPDATED: JUN 22, 2013 Pours clear amber with a medium, frothy off-white head, short retention with light lacing. Aroma is pear and apple esters, spicy rye malt, earthy pine hops. Flavor is crisp malt, light hops and bitterness with a dry finish. Medium body and carbonation.

On tap at Christian Firtal. Golden with a lasting white head. Aroma of malt, caramel, bourbon and alcohol. Sweet malty flavour with notable bourbon, a touch of sugar and quite a bit of alcohol. Too much
Tap @ C4, Odense. Pours ruby amber with a small off White head. Heavy sweetness. Massive caramel and vanilla. Wood. Boozy.

On tap @ Copenhagen Beer Celebration 2013. As good as black in the glass with a small islandy and sidesticking dark brown top. Lot of sweet licorice on the nose, in get a salty touch also with roasted malts and traces of chocolate paper. Much more roasted and smoked in the taste. Light almost cloudy on the mouthfeel and about average on the carbonation. Sweet ham, lots of unharmful chili, licorice before it ends in a dry and mouthdrying finish and aftertaste. 04.05.2013

Tap @ CBC 2013. The pours light amber with a small head. The aromas of toffee, toasted grain, sweet apple sauce. Spiced cake. Mild damson and plum. The taste is boozy raisin, treacle. Some vanilla. Fruit by the foot candy. Spicy. Pretty light body, aggressively carbed. Overall, not bad.

Served at CBC. Hazy dark amber look with a medium dense offwhite head. Aroma of wood, vanilla, toffee, rye and light roasted, even smoked malts. Flavor is quite sweet, again toffee and wood/bourbon with a roasted bitter finish.

Draught @ CBC 2013. Pours cloudy amber with a small frothy beige head. 
Aroma is caramel, spice, dried fruit, glue, rye, toasted malt, coconut, bread, green apple and flowers. Taste is moderate sweet, bitter and light tart. 
Body is light+, texture is thin, carbonation is moderate. Finishes sweet

Copenhagen Beer Celebration.
Tap, 040513.
Amber with off-white head. Aroma of malt and spices. Flavour with some caramel and sweetness (vanilla)

Sample at CBC 2013.

Orange colour with an off-white head. Aroma and flavour of spice, fruit, malt, caramel and hops.

UPDATED: APR 6, 2015 First rating: Small offwhite head.  Hazy deep dark red body. Perfumy plums and dried fruit aroma with spicy herbal apple notes. Dry-sweet alcoholic chocolate taste with nougat and vanilla notes. Mid-bodied. Sharpish mouthfeel. Dryish earthy wooden chocolatey aftertaste with vanilla alcohol notes. Nice, but a bit alcoholic. (0.2l draft at Crow Bar, Oslo.) 6,4,6,3,13=3.2

Second rating: Gusher. Which I would have caught in time, were it not for the
gimmicky feathers the brewers glued onto the neck of the bottle.
After mopping up, head is medium-sized and beige.  Funky earthy rye
aroma with metallic wooden notes.  Very aromatic, smelled it the whole
time while I was cleaning the table and the floor.  Sweetish mealy
chocolatey taste with wooden syrup notes.  Full-bodied.  Mild, soft,
slightly flat mouthfeel.  (Flat, huh? Now how could that be?)  Dryish
mealy chocolatey fruity aftertaste with funky earthy spicy notes.
Perhaps even a little cinnamon.  This was actually very nice.
Balanced and harmonic, and easy to drink.  After youve cleaned up,
that is.  (0.75l bottle, from Fish & Beer, Copenhagen.) 6,4,6,3,14=3.3

UPDATED: JUL 21, 2015 04.05.2013, tap @ CBC:
18.07.2015, 0,75l bottle shared @ BBGTC tasting:
Nice creamy mediumlasting head. Aroma is slightly dry grassy, rye, wet grass, caramel malts, weeds, sweaty cheese, oak, hay. Taste is slightly dry grassy, weeds, oak, rye, hay, caramel malts, old rope, bark. Medium to longlasting bitterness, slightly harsh and dry mouthfeel. Fair enough.

Tap at the Copenhagen Beer Celebration 2013. Poured an orange copper colour with a bubbly glass hugging head. The aroma is rich and oaky leading to a dry medium bitter flavour with some oak and whisky floating around there too. The palate is surprisingly smooth and the aftertaste a little watery. So many flavours and so many sensations! A super beer at the end of the day.

On tap at CBC 2013, Saturday evening, reddish with a light haze and a thin head, fruity spicy nose with faint marmalade hint, body is woody, with toasty rye but also barrel notes that catch in your mouth. A bit too cloying and out of balance.
Tap @ CBC. Dark amber with small off-white head. Aroma is malt, caramel, toffee, toasted and hop. Flavour is malt, caramel, medium sweet, toasted, toffee, hop and a little bitter.

De barril en el Kitsch (Gasteiz). Color ambar, buena corona de espuma. Aroma complejo, acaramelado. En boca, la entrada me recordó a una cerveza británica (frutos secos....), sigue con un sutil dulzor pero el final me resultó un poco decepcionante (jarabe para la tos).

De cualquier forma, tendría que darle otra oportunidad.

Draught at CBC 2013, cons 2013-05-04 Copenhagen
AR: plums, rasins, wee alcholic
AP: amber, no head
F: plum, wee hollow feeling, dry but sweet caramel
Sample @ CBC. Nice head with good duration. Color is amber. Aroma and taste are caramel, fruits, flowers, candy sugar, malt and hops.

On tap at CBC, pours a hazy orange amber with a small beige head. Aroma of dry caramel malts, rye malts, and dry bready malts. Flavour of rye malts, dry dark fruits, and bready malts. Very dry and bready, with a slight caramel tinge. Not the most interesting stuff, but acceptable. Decent.
A very simple beer. Taste and aroma of wood, bourbon and rye. Not much to complex, plain and a little boring.
Fat på CBC 2013. Smak och doft av humle, malt, karamell, smörkola med toner av vanilj ohc rök. Jämn och fin.

Draught at CBC 2013. En strong ale med mycket söta fruktiga malt och fatsmaker. Banankola, karamell, vanilj, bourbon och en lätt röktouch. Riktigt trevlig. Bra svagare alternativ till en barley wine. Spännande smakkombinationer.

Draught at CBC 2013. Dark amber beer with a decent head. Sourish aroma, caramel, Woody, whiskey, vanilla notes, grapes, some apples. Fruity sourish aroma, Woody, whiskey notes, vanilla, rye bread, hay, some warming alcohol.

Draught. Hazy deep amber liquid with small white head. Aroma of toffee, green apples, wood, caramel and grassy hops. Taste is dry and light to medium bitter with notes of toffee, citrus and pine. Medium bodied with medium carbonation.
Draft at charleston beer works. Rather flat muddy amber orange pour. Whiskey is pretty prevalent in both aroma and flavor. Wood, caramel maltiness too. Medium bodied. Decent
on draft, this one was a good amount of bourbon characteristics on a hoppy spicy amber beer. It worked very well

Draft at Jerry?s.  Dark copper with decent, creamy beige head (barrel-aged) / Sweet, sour, elegant nose of whiskey barrel, caramel, dark fruit, turning orchard fruit / Medium body, lean, smooth, some chew, some woody astringency,  lovely balance with a hint of bitterness on the finish / Stylish, complex flavors of caramel, turning red apple, bourbon barrel, raisin, licorice / Great, great stuff.

Draught. Pours a slightly hazy amber color with a moderate head. Nose has lots of rye in there and implies a fair amount of bitterness. Taste is actually a little heavy and filled with grains. I find this a bit odd...

25th September 2012Craft. Hazy deep amber beer, little pale cream coloured head. Palate is smooth and soft with fine carbonation. Massive barrel character here. But the beers starts with some acetic apples and pears. Then loads of soft vanilla and toasted coconut and very mild tangy rye whisky. Trace of wood. Mild estery bubblegum before the smooth semi dry finish. Ian Harrison would describe this as barrelled to within and inch of its life.

On tap at CBC, London. It pours a dark amber color with a small off-white head. Aroma is straight up whiskey. Crazy. Like smelling a glass of Jack Daniel.. Some vanilla and malty notes as well. Taste is sweet-ish with a final bitter kick to it. Whiskey all over the place. Plus some hops. Mouthfeel is medium with soft carbonation. Wow, like drinking a good whiskey at 7%ABV only!

Tap at Craft Beer Co Clerkenwell - 26/09/12.
Slightly hazy copper brown with a small off-white head.
Bourbon on the nose straight off with wood tones and a little lemon.
The bourbon is more subtle in the taste, again woody, some malt and ry.
Palate is the lighter end of medium bodied with matching carbonation, if anything a little too thin for a 7%+ ABV beer with some complex flavours to it!
user_location: Hazlemere, the lower Xhitlerns, Buckinghamshire, ENGLAND

text: Draught @ craft beer co. Pours deep amber. Small white head. Aroma: you definitely get the bourbon. Loads of malty sweetness, caramel, dried fruits. Especially plums, raisins and fig. Earthy notes and wood. Very fruity. Taste follows through. Mouth feel is medium, some yeasty notes, cloves and even a hint of banana. rye, and slight smoke. Taste is quite sweet, but the bourbon keeps it interesting.

Draft @ Bishops Arms, Copenhagen. Pours a slightly hazy amber color with a small off-white head. Has a fruity malty caramel aroma with woody vanilla hints. Fruity malty caramel and vanilla flavor. Has a fruity malty woody caramel finish with hints of vanilla.

From tap at Bishops Arms. Pours clear and golden deep amber with a small off white head. Aroma is fruity and toasted malt. Light yeasty, caramelish toasted malty. Toffee caramelish and light fruity into a toasted malty finish.

Draught at Bishops Arms, CPH. Clear amber/red - white head.
Amber malty. Light boozy. Fruity. Ok wooden notes. Vanilla. Light coconut. Spicy. Rye. Rather sweet. Cocoa. Light smokey notes. Ok bitterness. High fruity. Dried fruits.

Draught at Bishops Arms.
Cloudy amber coloured with a medium sized off-white head.
Sweet and fruity aroma of caramel, cookies and dried fruits.
Sweet and fruity flavour of caramel, dried fruits, bourbon and alcohol.
Warming alcoholic finish.
Draft. An amber beer with a dense off-white head. The aroma has notes malt and caramel. The flavor is sweet with notes of caramel, rye, malt, and dusty hops, leading to a dry finish.

Tap @ Bishops Arms, Copenhagen. Clear dark amber with an off-white head. Aroma is sweet, malty, rye, caramel and moderate hoppy. Flavor is quite sweet and moderate bitter. Sweet finish. Smooth and soft. 240412

1 L growler shared by Tmoney99.  Pours a clear deep amber color with a small fine white head.  The aroma has sweet caramel, vanilla, spicy rye notes, hints of ripe fruit and of course the bourbon barrel.  The flavor has toasted rye bread splashed with caramel, vanilla, the barrel notes are more mild than the nose would indicate and the finish is a bit soft.  This was good, but needs a little something through the finish to take it over the top.
thanks to ratebeer, i see now, local option and Against the Grain have a special relationship.

Pours clear pale red with a very strong 2 finger head.  Aroma is fresh bourbon barrel vanilla, rye breadiness, dominated by barrel notes.  Taste is a perfect blend of sour-ish bourbon notes and rustic rye breadiness; some biscuit, some ethanol.  Body is medium, silky smooth, medium carbonation, long woody finish.  Overall, very tasty.

Draft. Deep amber body with a short off-white head. Aroma mostly bourbon, but not enough to completely mask notes of rye, wood. The flavor is moderately sweet and lightly bitter. It finishes lightly to moderately sweet and moderately bitter. Medium body, velvety texture and moderately to lively carbonation. The alcohol, though only 7%, is apparent in the finish. Bourbon taste mostly, but a taste of rye bread underlies it. Lacks complexity. Easy drinking.
Draught at brewpub. Ale with strong whiskey/bourbon flavor. Coconut. Barrel really put a lot of flavor into this one, a little much overall, but it is tasty.

Aroma of rye malts, bourbon and almonds. Appearance is red with bone head. Flavor is right on the nose; though the bourbon shines through more than the rye malts, imo. The finish is slightly resiny a little booze. Palate is bubbly with slight liveliness. Interesting beer; I wish I were able to pick up a little more fruit as mentioned in the description.

Tap (growler).  Rye bread and alcohol aroma.  Reddish amber color with moderate head.  Lightly sweet rye malt and lightly bitter herbal flavor.  Light alcohol finish.  Nice - a bit boozy and rye flavor on the light side but an easy drinking beer.

Growler. Poured a dark copper color with a minimal bubble off-white head that mostly diminished with little lacing. Moderate to heavy complex hop and bourbon wood aroma. Medium body and a smooth texture and flat carbonation. Medium to heavy bittersweet flavor with a medium bittersweet finish of moderate duration. Soft drinkable brew.
